<div class="md-help">
    <h3>Markdown help</h3>
    <h4>Headers</h4>
    <p>Markdown supports 2 styles of headers</p>
    <ul>
        <li>This is an H1
            =============

            This is an H2
            -------------
        </li>
        <li># This is an H1

            ## This is an H2

            ###### This is an H6
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Lists</h4>
    <p>Markdown supports ordered (numbered) and unordered (bulleted) lists.</p>
    <p>Unordered lists use asterisks, pluses, and hyphens — interchangably — as list markers:</p>
    <p>Ordered lists use numbers followed by periods:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>*   Red
            *   Green
            *   Blue
        </li>
        <li>+   Red
            +   Green
            +   Blue
        </li>
        <li>-   Red
            -   Green
            -   Blue
        </li>
        <li>1.  Bird
            2.  McHale
            3.  Parish
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Quotes</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>&gt; This is a blockquote with some text.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Can be nested or contain other markdown elements</p>
    <ul>
        <li>&gt; ## This is a header.
            &gt;
            &gt; 1.   This is the first list item.
            &gt; 2.   This is the second list item.
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>